OL,5, A 93-year-old lollipop man has said he 
OL,6, has had his lifeline cut after being   
OL,7, made redundant as part of council cuts.
OL,9,FAlfred Tollon from Romford has been    
OL,10,Fhelping pupils cross the road at Harrow
OL,11,FLodge Primary School for 24 years.     
OL,13,FHe said his job had kept him motivated 
OL,14,Fafter his wife died and it was "the    
OL,15,Fchildren that make my day".            
OL,17,FMr Tollon even offered to work for free
OL,18,Fbut he said Havering Council told him  
OL,19,Fthe cost of insuring him was           
OL,20,Fprohibitive.                           
